---
const _keywords = [
	// One-word keywords
	"devpad",
	"tasks",
	"projects",
	"management",
	"developers",

	// Two-word keywords
	"project management",
	"task tracking",
	"code scanning",
	"github integration",
	"todo comments",
	"developer tools",
	"task automation",
	"project visibility",
	"api integration",
	"task filtering",
	"project updates",
	"task priorities",
	"codebase tasks",
	"project milestones",
	"task editor",
	"project goals",

	// Three-word keywords
	"developer project management",
	"github task tracking",
	"todo comment scanning",
	"project management api",
	"task management tools",
];
---

<Layout
	title="devpad"
	description="devpad.tools provides project and task management for developers. The main feature is automatic scanning of github repos to extract the todo comments"
	keywords={keywords}
	canonical="https://devpad.tools"
>
	<body>
		<main class="landing-page" style="display: grid; gap: 100px; width: 80vw; max-width: 1000px; justify-items: center; justify-content: center;">
			<div></div>
			<br />
			<section id="hero" style="width: 100%">
				<h1 class="flex-row" style="gap: 20px; justify-content: center;">
					<DevpadLogo size={48} />
					<span style="font-size: 3rem;">devpad</span>
				</h1>
				<div style="height: 75px"></div>
				<div class="mobile-grid">
					<div style="width: 100%; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
						<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; text-align: center">
							scan & track <code>@todo</code> comments
						</p>
						<p style="margin-top: -19px; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-tertiary)">& way more</p>
						<div style="font-size: 1.2rem">
							<GithubLogin size={30} client:load />
						</div>
					</div>
					<img src="/hero-scan.png" alt="Scan codebase into tasks" />
				</div>
			</section>
			<br />
			<section id="projects" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;">
				<h2 style="text-align: center">project management</h2>
				<div class="mobile-grid">
					<p>
						devpad offers a dead simple yet powerful way to manage your ever-increasing list of projects. with options for visibility, development progress, and the abiltiy to
						specify separate github & deployment links for each project, all of your projects can be managed in a single place. when linking to a github repo, devpad offers the
						ability to scan the codebase for tasks, automatically updating, creating or deleting tasks for you.
						<a style="margin-top: 10px;" class="flex-row" href="/project">
							<span>projects</span>
							<ExternalLink />
						</a>
					</p>
					<img src="/project-creator.png" alt="project creator dialog" />
					<img src="/project-api.png" alt="devpad projects api" />
					<p>
						when all your projects have been setup, you can make use of devpad's built-in api to query your projects, perfect for integrating with your portfolio website, or other
						projects. with this api, you can build your own extensions, keeping this application as the only place to manage your projects.
						<a style="margin-top: 10px;" class="flex-row" href="/docs">
							<span>api docs</span>
							<ExternalLink />
						</a>
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section id="tasks" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;">
				<h2 style="text-align: center">task management</h2>
				<div class="mobile-grid">
					<p>
						keeping track of everything you need to do for a project is a pain. devpad offers a simple way to add new tasks, attach them to a project, and add a summary,
						description, give due dates and assign priorities. when integrated with the project manager, you can update these tasks automatically directly from the comments in your
						codebase, with just enough user verification to make sure everything is how you want it.
						<a style="margin-top: 10px;" class="flex-row" href="/todo">
							<span>tasks</span>
							<ExternalLink />
						</a>
					</p>
					<img src="/task-view.png" alt="Task grid view" />
					<img src="/scan-update.png" alt="Update dialog for task scanning" />
					<p>
						the task editor allows you to assign tags to each tasks, allowing for powerful searching & filtering. similar to the project manager, all of this data is available via
						the built-in api, allowing you to hook into your task list from anywhere. the possibilties are endless.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<!-- TODO: add testimonials 

        id="testimonials"
        style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;"
      >
        <h2 style="text-align: center">testimonials</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;">
          
        </div>
      </section>
      <br /> -->
			<section id="how-it-works" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;">
				<h2 style="text-align: center">how it works</h2>
				<div class="triple-grid">
					<div>
						<img src="/import-project.png" alt="Import project from github" />
						<p>1. import project</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<img src="/check-for-updates.png" alt="Scan repo for updates" />
						<p>2. check for updates</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<img src="/scan-updates.png" alt="Accept updates from scan" />
						<p>3. accept updates</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			<br />
			<section id="end" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px; align-items: center;">
				<h2 style="text-align: center">let's get started</h2>
				<GithubLogin size={30} client:load />
			</section>
			<br />
			<br />
		</main>
		<footer>
			<p>Â© 2025 devpad</p>
		</footer>
	</body>
</Layout>
